						<summary>

						<p>This inscription is built in at the end. It seems to record that Sundaranāḍan, a devotee (<hi rend="italic">ṭiruvēgambaḍiyār</hi>) residing at the temple complex (<hi rend="italic">tirumaḍaiviḷāgam</hi>) deposited certain amount in the temple treasury and the interest accrued out of this amount as millet was to be utilized for providing food offerings and for the procession of the deity.</p>						

						</summary>
